Charles Czeisler, sleep medicine professor at Harvard Medical School and specialist at Brigham and Women's Hospital, was the author of the course, who believes to be the first of his type in the United States.
The inspiration for the course emerged after having given a lecture on the impact of sleep deprivation on learning.
"In the end, a girl came to me and said, "Why are you just telling me this in the last year of the course?"
